tk@ai.mit.edu (Tom Knight) writes:
>Arrrgh.  Once more with feeling.  You need not use ONE CD as the one
>time pad -- you can XOR *many* CDs and use the result as a one time
>pad.

	Please do not abuse the terminology by referring to your
suggestion as a "one time pad."   It is not. It's something else,
and it has very different properties. Namely, it's nowhere near
as secure.

	Can we stop referring to all these hokum schemes involving
long-period key systems as "one time pads"??

